Basics in Order:


Variable basics:
    Datatypes
        -int, double, boolean, String, short, long, byte
        -cast one datatype to another with ()

    Operators
        -+, -, *, /, %
        -++, --

    Expressions
        Include operands and operators
    


How to use your data:
    System.out.println();
    
    Scanner scanner = new Scanner();

    Math class (Math.max, Math.min, Math.abs, Math.sqrt, Math.pi for starters)

    Random random = new Random();

    Parts of a statement
        -() are parameters
            -use , if it takes multiple parameters
        -{} are the contents
        
    If Statements
        -<, >, <=, >=, ==
        -else if
        --&&, ||, !

    Switch Statements
        switch () {
            case value:
                
                break;
        
            default:
                break;
        }
    
    Loops
        -While Loops
            -while () {}
            -Loops as long as the condition is true
        -For Loops
            -for ( , , ) {}
            -Loops a limited number of times
        -Nested Loops
    
    Arrays
        -DATATYPE[] VARIABLENAME
            -= {};, or = new DATATYPE();
            -[][][][][] Multiple Dimensions
        
